<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,488,670]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,488,514]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Discussion:</emphasis>
The description of this species is not sufficient for a clear idea of its diagnostic features (
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow" pageId="13" pageNumber="33" refString="Sokolow, I. (1940) Hydracarina (1. re partie: Hydrachnellae). In: Sernow, A. &amp; Stackelberg, A. (eds.), Faune de l'URSS. Arachnides. Institute de l'Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscow, Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1940">
Sokolow 
<number box="[151,215,528,554]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In his attempt at a redescription, 
<bibRefCitation author="Biesiadka" box="[626,828,528,554]" pageId="13" pageNumber="31" refString="Biesiadka, E. (1972) Wodopojki (Hydracarina) Wielkopolskiego Parku Narodowego. (Hydracarina of the National Park of Great Poland). Prace Monograficzne. nad Przyroda Wielkopolskiego Parku Narodowego pod Poznaniem, 5 (3), 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1972">
Biesiadka (
<number box="[759,820,528,554]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized a similarity to 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1262,528,553]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1262,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. planus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species that was collected on the same occasion and at the same site, but did not mention clearcut diagnostic differences between these two taxa. As the 
<typeStatus box="[539,645,605,631]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[687,862,605,630]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peroviensis">
<emphasis box="[687,862,605,630]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. peroviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lost, a redescription and interpretation of its characteristics is impossible and it must be regarded as 
<emphasis box="[801,976,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
species 
<taxonomicName box="[893,976,644,669]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Todothyas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incerta">incerta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
